                <div class="info-card">
                    <h4><i class="fas fa-wave-square"></i> Manchester Encoding (10 Mbps)</h4>
                    <p>Each data bit requires two signal transitions. Provides excellent clock recovery but limits throughput due to increased signaling overhead.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <h4><i class="fas fa-exchange-alt"></i> 4B/5B Encoding (100 Mbps)</h4>
                    <p>Every four data bits are encoded as five signal bits, improving efficiency while maintaining clock recovery capability.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <h4><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> 8B/10B Encoding (1 Gbps)</h4>
                    <p>Eight data bits encoded as ten signal bits provides optimal efficiency for high-speed transmission while preserving DC balance.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <h4><i class="fas fa-cable"></i> Transmission Media Characteristics</h4>
                    <ul>
